lesConfNextId.name: lesConfNextId
lesConfNextId.description: The next available LES index. The value of this object can be used as the index by the network manager to create an entry in the lesConfTable.

lesConfTable.name: lesConfTable
lesConfTable.description: This table contains all LAN Emulation Servers this agent manages. The LES is one of the components in the Emulated LAN which implements the control coordination function. It is the address resolution server for a given ELAN. The LES provides a facility for registering and resolving MAC addresses and/or route descriptors to ATM addresses. There can be multiple LES per ELAN but a LES can serve only one ELAN.

lesConfEntry.name: lesConfEntry
lesConfEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a LES. The parameters in each entry apply to one emulated LAN served by one LES. Objects lesLanType and lesMaxFrameSize are also required besides lesRowStatus during row creation.

lesConfIndex.name: lesConfIndex
lesConfIndex.description: A value which uniquely identifies a conceptual row in the lesConfTable. If the conceptual row identified by this value of lesConfIndex is recreated following an agent restart, the same value of lesConfIndex must be used to identify the recreated row.

lesAtmAddrSpec.name: lesAtmAddrSpec
lesAtmAddrSpec.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. S1.
lesAtmAddrSpec.description: An ATM address specified by the network or local management that, with the ATM address mask, determines a portion of the ATM address that the LES on the designated ATM interface will use to derive the actual ATM address from the network or ILMI. The derived ATM address is specified in the object lesAtmAddrActual, which is used to receive ATM ARP requests.

lesAtmAddrMask.name: lesAtmAddrMask
lesAtmAddrMask.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. S1.
lesAtmAddrMask.description: The ATM address mask associated with the object lesAtmAddrSpec. The value of the mask is an ATM address with the don't care portion set to zero and the valid ATM address portion set to one.

lesAtmAddrActual.name: lesAtmAddrActual
lesAtmAddrActual.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. S1.
lesAtmAddrActual.description: The resultant ATM address in use by the LES. This object is a product of the specified ATM address, mask and interaction with the network. This object is created by the agent.

lesElanName.name: lesElanName
lesElanName.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. C5.
lesElanName.description: The name of the Emulated LAN this LES is providing service for. This object may be used to identify the ELAN the LES is in.

lesLanType.name: lesLanType
lesLanType.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. S2.
lesLanType.description: The type of the ATM Emulated LAN this LES is providing service to.

lesLastChange.name: lesLastChange
lesLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when this LES has entered the state indicated by the object lesOperStatus.

lesMaxFrameSize.name: lesMaxFrameSize
lesMaxFrameSize.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. S3.
lesMaxFrameSize.description: The maximum AAL-5 SDU size of a data frame that the LE service can guarantee not to drop because it is too large.

lesControlTimeOut.name: lesControlTimeOut
lesControlTimeOut.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. S4.
lesControlTimeOut.description: Time out period used for timing out most request/response control frame interactions. This is the time a Client has to issue a join request to a LES after a control direct VCC is established with a LES.

lesOperStatus.name: lesOperStatus
lesOperStatus.description: The operational state of this LES entry. When in 'up' state the LES will respond to LEC requests. Any other state the LES is notavailable for service and may release all the existing VCCs and refuse service to all clients.

lesAdminStatus.name: lesAdminStatus
lesAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the designated LES as prescribed by the operator. The actions of the agent will, if at all possible, eventually result in the desired state being reflected in the lesOperStatus.

lesRowStatus.name: lesRowStatus
lesRowStatus.reference: RFC 1443, [10] Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).
lesRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in the elanConfTable.

lesVccTable.name: lesVccTable
lesVccTable.description: This table contains all the Control Distribute VCCs used by the LES to distribute control traffic to the participating LECs. The Control Distribute VCC can either be point-to-point or point-to- multipoint calls. This table is read only if SVCs are used and writable if PVCs are used.

lesVccEntry.name: lesVccEntry
lesVccEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a LES entry and it's associated Control Distribute VCC.

lesVccAtmIfIndex.name: lesVccAtmIfIndex
lesVccAtmIfIndex.description: The ATM interface which the Control Distribute VCC is running on. This value must match an existing value in the ifTable. The value of this object is set to zero when the ATM interface is an internal connection.

lesVccCtlDistVpi.name: lesVccCtlDistVpi
lesVccCtlDistVpi.description: The VPI value of the Control Distribute VCC. The object lesVccAtmIfIndex, lesVccCtlDistVci and the value of this object uniquely identfies a VCC within a ATM host.

lesVccCtlDistVci.name: lesVccCtlDistVci
lesVccCtlDistVci.description: The VCI value of the Control Distribute VCC. The object lesVccAtmIfIndex, lesVccCtlDistVci and the value of this object uniquely identfies a VCC within a ATM host.

lesVccRowStatus.name: lesVccRowStatus
lesVccRowStatus.reference: RFC 1443, [10] Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).
lesVccRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in the elanConfTable.

lesBusTable.name: lesBusTable
lesBusTable.description: This table contains the BUSs paired with the LESs found in the lesConfTable. The BUS (Broadcast and Unknown Server) handles data sent by a LE client to the broadcast MAC address, all multicast traffic, and initial unicast frames which are sent by a LAN Emulation Client before the data direct target ATM address has been resolved.

lesBusEntry.name: lesBusEntry
lesBusEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents aLES/BUS pair. Object lesBusAddress is required duringrow creation. This table is indexed by lesConfIndex and lesBusConfIndexto show the pairing relationship betweenthe LES and BUS.

lesBusConfIndex.name: lesBusConfIndex
lesBusConfIndex.description: A value which uniquely identifies a BUS ATM address. If the BUS ATM address identified by this value of lesBusConfIndex is recreated following an agent restart, the same value of lesBusConfIndex must be used to identify the recreated BUS ATM address.

lesBusAddress.name: lesBusAddress
lesBusAddress.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. S6.
lesBusAddress.description: The ATM address of the BUS. This BUS is associated with LES specified by the lesConfIndex. A BUS may have several ATM addresses, this object provides the ATM address the LES returns in response to the LE-ARP request by the LEC.

lesLeArpMacTable.name: lesLeArpMacTable
lesLeArpMacTable.description: This table provides access to an ATM LAN Emulation Server's MAC-to-ATM ARP table. It contains entries for unicast addressed, the broadcast address. When the entry is for broadcast MAC address the corresponding ATM address is of a BUS. When the entry is for unicast MAC address the corresponding ATM address represents a LEC.

lesLeArpMacEntry.name: lesLeArpMacEntry
lesLeArpMacEntry.description: An ATM LAN Emulation ARP table entry containing information about the binding of one MAC address to one ATM address.

lesLeArpMacAddr.name: lesLeArpMacAddr
lesLeArpMacAddr.description: The MAC address for which this table entry provides a translation. Since ATM LAN Emulation uses an LE ARP protocol to locate the Broadcast and Unknown Server, the value of this object could be the broadcast MAC address. MAC addresses should be unique within any given ATM Emulated LAN. However, there's no requirement that they be unique across disjoint emulated LANs.

lesLeArpLecId.name: lesLeArpLecId
lesLeArpLecId.description: The LE Client Identifier (LECID) of this entry. Each LE Client requires a LECID assigned by the LE Server during the Join phase. If this entry is for a BUS then this object value will be zero.

lesLeArpAtmAddr.name: lesLeArpAtmAddr
lesLeArpAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the Broadcast & Unknown Server or LAN Emulation Client whose MAC address is stored in 'lesLeArpMacAddr'. This volume may be registered by a LAN Emulation Client or specified by network management.

lesLeArpEntryType.name: lesLeArpEntryType
lesLeArpEntryType.description: This object is used to indicate how this LE-ARP entry was created. The possible values for this object are: viaRegister(1), - agent staticVolatile(2), - network manager staticNonVolatile(3) - network manager This object is filled in by agent or network manager depending on the type.

lesLeArpRowStatus.name: lesLeArpRowStatus
lesLeArpRowStatus.reference: RFC 1443, [10] Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).
lesLeArpRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in the elanConfTable.

lesLeArpRdTable.name: lesLeArpRdTable
lesLeArpRdTable.description: This table provides access to an ATM LAN Emulation Server's RouteDescriptor-to-ATM ARP cache. The entries in this table are set-up by the agent or network manager depending on the entry type. The Route Descriptors are presented as Segment Id (ring number) and Bridge number.

lesLeArpRdEntry.name: lesLeArpRdEntry
lesLeArpRdEntry.description: An ATM LAN Emulation ARP cache entry containing information about the binding of one Route Descriptor to one ATM address.

lesLeArpRdSegId.name: lesLeArpRdSegId
lesLeArpRdSegId.description: The LAN ID (ring number) portion of the IEEE 802.5 route descriptor associated with this LES.

lesLeArpRdBridgeNum.name: lesLeArpRdBridgeNum
lesLeArpRdBridgeNum.description: The Bridge Number portion of the IEEE 802.5 route descriptor associated with this LES.

lesLeArpRdLecId.name: lesLeArpRdLecId
lesLeArpRdLecId.description: The LE Client Identifier (LECID) of this entry. Each LE Client requires a LECID assigned by the LE Server during the Join phase.

lesLeArpRdAtmAddr.name: lesLeArpRdAtmAddr
lesLeArpRdAtmAddr.description: The ATM address associated with the Route Descriptor.

lesLeArpRdEntryType.name: lesLeArpRdEntryType
lesLeArpRdEntryType.description: This object is used to indicate how this LE-ARP entry was learned: viaRegister(1), - agent staticVolatile(2), - network manager staticNonVolatile(3) - network manager This object is filled in by agent or network manager depending on the type.

lesLeArpRdRowStatus.name: lesLeArpRdRowStatus
lesLeArpRdRowStatus.reference: RFC 1443, [10] Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).
lesLeArpRdRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in the elanConfTable.

lesLecTableLastChange.name: lesLecTableLastChange
lesLecTableLastChange.description: The value of sysUptime when an entry was created/deleted.

lesLecTable.name: lesLecTable
lesLecTable.description: This table contains all LAN Emulation clients serviced by LESs specified in the lesConfTable. This table can be used to retrieve the topology of an ELAN, in particular, the LES to LECs mapping information. An entry in this table is filled in by the agent when a LEC registers successfully with the LES. Objects lesLecCtlDirectVpi and lesLecCtlDirectVci can be modified by the network manager after creation if PVC is used.

lesLecEntry.name: lesLecEntry
lesLecEntry.description: Each entry represents a LANE client to LES binding.

lesLecIndex.name: lesLecIndex
lesLecIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquely identifies a LEC in this table.

lesLecAtmAddr.name: lesLecAtmAddr
lesLecAtmAddr.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.3
lesLecAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the LANE client. This is the primary ATM address of the LEC used in joining phase.

lesLecProxy.name: lesLecProxy
lesLecProxy.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
lesLecProxy.description: Whether this client is acting as a proxy. Proxy clients are allowed to represent unregistered MAC addresses, and receive copies of LE_ARP_REQUEST packets for such addresses.

lesLecId.name: lesLecId
lesLecId.description: The LE Client Identifier (LECID) of this entry. Each LE Client requires a LECID assigned by the LE Server during the Join phase. The LECID is placed in control requests by the LE Client and MAY be used for echo suppression on multicast data frames sent by that LE Client.

lesLecAtmIfIndex.name: lesLecAtmIfIndex
lesLecAtmIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of ATM port where this LEC entry has established the control direct VCC to the LES. The value of this object maps to an existing ifIndex value in the ifTable of MIB-II. When an internal connection is used, this object is set to zero.

lesLecCtlDirectVpi.name: lesLecCtlDirectVpi
lesLecCtlDirectVpi.description: The VPI of the bi-directional control direct connection between the LEC and LES.

lesLecCtlDirectVci.name: lesLecCtlDirectVci
lesLecCtlDirectVci.description: The VCI of the bi-directional control direct connection between the LEC and LES.

lesLecLastChange.name: lesLecLastChange
lesLecLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime of this entry when the LEC enters the state indicated by the object lesLecState.

lesLecState.name: lesLecState
lesLecState.description: This object is used to indicate the status this LEC entry is in from the LES's perspective. The state of this object is updated by the agent as it discovers various phases of this LEC.

lesLecRowStatus.name: lesLecRowStatus
lesLecRowStatus.reference: RFC 1443, [10] Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).
lesLecRowStatus.description: This object provides a way for the network manager to selectively remove a LE Client from the designated LES. Or in a system where PVCs are used, this table is used to configure Control Direct VCCs between LES and LEC.

lesStatTable.name: lesStatTable
lesStatTable.description: This table contains all counters the LES maintain. This table is an extention to the lesConfTable. It provides performance and fault counters on a per LES basis.

lesStatEntry.name: lesStatEntry
lesStatEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains a LES and its counters.

lesStatJoinOk.name: lesStatJoinOk
lesStatJoinOk.description: Number of successful Join responses send out by the LAN Emulation Server.

lesStatVerNotSup.name: lesStatVerNotSup
lesStatVerNotSup.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Table 13.
lesStatVerNotSup.description: Number of version not supported errors.

lesStatInvalidReqParam.name: lesStatInvalidReqParam
lesStatInvalidReqParam.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Table 13.
lesStatInvalidReqParam.description: Number of invalid request parameters errors.

lesStatDupLanDest.name: lesStatDupLanDest
lesStatDupLanDest.description: Number of duplicate LAN destination errors.

lesStatDupAtmAddr.name: lesStatDupAtmAddr
lesStatDupAtmAddr.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Table 13.
lesStatDupAtmAddr.description: Number of duplicate ATM address errors.

lesStatInsRes.name: lesStatInsRes
lesStatInsRes.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Table 13.
lesStatInsRes.description: Number of insufficient resources to grant errors.

lesStatAccDenied.name: lesStatAccDenied
lesStatAccDenied.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Table 13.
lesStatAccDenied.description: Number of access denied for security reasons errors.

lesStatInvalidReqId.name: lesStatInvalidReqId
lesStatInvalidReqId.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Table 13.
lesStatInvalidReqId.description: Number of invalid LEC ID errors.

lesStatInvalidLanDest.name: lesStatInvalidLanDest
lesStatInvalidLanDest.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Table 13.
lesStatInvalidLanDest.description: Number of invalid LAN destination errors.

lesStatInvalidAtmAddr.name: lesStatInvalidAtmAddr
lesStatInvalidAtmAddr.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Table 13.
lesStatInvalidAtmAddr.description: Number of invalid ATM address errors.

lesStatInBadPkts.name: lesStatInBadPkts
lesStatInBadPkts.description: Number of mal formed ATM ARP requests received by the LES.

lesStatOutRegFails.name: lesStatOutRegFails
lesStatOutRegFails.description: Number of registration failures sent out by this LES.

lesStatLeArpIn.name: lesStatLeArpIn
lesStatLeArpIn.description: The total number of LE_ARP_REQUEST frames the LES has accepted since its last initialization.

lesStatLeArpFwd.name: lesStatLeArpFwd
lesStatLeArpFwd.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs that the LES forwarded onto the clients (either via the control distribute or individually over each control direct) rather than answering directly. This may be due to implementation decision (forward all requests) or because the resolution to the request did not reside in the LES's LE ARP cache.

lesLecStatTable.name: lesLecStatTable
lesLecStatTable.description: This table contains all LE-ARP request related counters and error counts on a per LEC-LES pair basis.

lesLecStatEntry.name: lesLecStatEntry
lesLecStatEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a LEC and its ARP counters. This table is an extention to the lesLecTable.

lesLecRecvs.name: lesLecRecvs
lesLecRecvs.description: Number of requests received from this LEC. This includes all control frames as well as LE-ARP requests.

lesLecSends.name: lesLecSends
lesLecSends.description: Number of requests or responses sent to the LEC entry from this LES.

lesLecInRegReq.name: lesLecInRegReq
lesLecInRegReq.description: Number of Register requests received from this LEC.

lesLecInUnReg.name: lesLecInUnReg
lesLecInUnReg.description: Number of UnRegister requests received from this LEC.

lesLecInLeArpUcast.name: lesLecInLeArpUcast
lesLecInLeArpUcast.description: Number of LE-ARP requests for UNICAST address received from this LEC.

lesLecInLeArpBcast.name: lesLecInLeArpBcast
lesLecInLeArpBcast.description: Number of LE-ARP requests for MULTICAST and Broadcast address received from this LEC.

lesLecInLeArpResp.name: lesLecInLeArpResp
lesLecInLeArpResp.description: Number of LE-ARP responses received from this LEC.

lesLecInNarp.name: lesLecInNarp
lesLecInNarp.description: Number of NARP requests received from this LEC.

lesErrCtlTable.name: lesErrCtlTable
lesErrCtlTable.description: This table contains error log control information of all LES instances. This table is an extention to the lesConfTable. It is used to enable or disable error logs for a particular LES entry.

lesErrCtlEntry.name: lesErrCtlEntry
lesErrCtlEntry.description: Each entry represents a LES entry in the lesConfTable.

lesErrCtlAdminStatus.name: lesErrCtlAdminStatus
lesErrCtlAdminStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable error logging for the LES.

lesErrCtlOperStatus.name: lesErrCtlOperStatus
lesErrCtlOperStatus.description: This object is used to indicate the result of a set operation to the object lesErrCtlAdminStatus. If the error log was successfully started, it is in active(2) mode. Otherwise, it is set to either outOfRes(3) or failed(4) for the respective reasons.

lesErrCtlClearLog.name: lesErrCtlClearLog
lesErrCtlClearLog.description: This object is used to clear the error log entries associated with this LES.

lesErrCtlMaxEntries.name: lesErrCtlMaxEntries
lesErrCtlMaxEntries.description: The maximum entries of the error log a LES can support.

lesErrCtlLastEntry.name: lesErrCtlLastEntry
lesErrCtlLastEntry.description: The index to the last entry in the error log table for this LES.

lesErrLogTable.name: lesErrLogTable
lesErrLogTable.description: This table contains error logs of the LES instances enabled in the lesErrCtlTable. This table is indexed by the LES instance index and an arbitrary integer uniquely identifies an error log.

lesErrLogEntry.name: lesErrLogEntry
lesErrLogEntry.description: Each entry represents a JOIN or REGISTER that was rejected due to an error.

lesErrLogIndex.name: lesErrLogIndex
lesErrLogIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquely identifies an error log entry. The first entry after reset or clearing the error log is an assigned value (2^32-1). Succeding entries are assigned with descending values consecutively. Entries after 1 are discarded. The enabling/disabling of the error log capability is done in the lesErrCtlTable.

lesErrLogAtmAddr.name: lesErrLogAtmAddr
lesErrLogAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the requester which sends the JOIN or REGISTER request and causes the error to occur. The corresponding error code is specified in the object lesErrLogErrCode.

lesErrLogErrCode.name: lesErrLogErrCode
lesErrLogErrCode.description: The Error code which indicates the cause of the error triggered by the JOIN or REGISTER request sent by the requester indicated by the value of the object lesErrLogAtmAddr.

lesErrLogTime.name: lesErrLogTime
lesErrLogTime.description: The sysUpTime when this entry was logged by the LES.
